Hi,
Aldo has given you the most likely solution but we have found when
a group member has, by mistake, used another of their addresses other
than the listed version, that it has in fact been delivered to
everyone. The only difference being it did not appear in the web site.
Our group is set as private and so this is a problem that may affect
public groups more. Perhaps it would not be a bad idea if  the address
of a message sent to the group was checked against the master list and
only forwarded on if  listed. Having you group name publicly known
could be a reason for spam coming into your group.
Regards
Reg

