<POSTDATE> 2007-11-05T08:57:00 </POSTDATE>
Hello Reg,

All that you're telling depends on your group settings.
If in your group &quot;anybody can see the group content&quot; and &quot;anyone can
post&quot;, it's obvious you're receiving posts from spammers too. Even if
you're requiring an invitation request.....it's contradictory!
Begin to set the group to &quot;only members can see group content&quot; and
&quot;only members can post&quot;, you'll see things in a very different way. At
this point, you could also set the group to &quot;anyone can
join&quot;.....provided that &quot;new members
are moderated&quot;, you can easily control if the person who just joined
is a spammer or not.

By the way, this can also explain because you're believing to have a
lot of members, all automatically verified (do you recall our last
conversation?).
Truly, you're having just a few &quot;full&quot; members, who joined clicking on
the UNIQUE link of their invitation, because they had already a Google
group account!
The other ones aren't prompted to do quite a work, because they're
already able to see the group content, and/or to post.

My apologies if I'm wrong, and I didn't find your right group.....but
I don't think so. The matter is your group is anomalous and, sorry,
your advices can be misleading for other group owners.

My apologies again if I've been harsh.....but this needed to be said.

Regards
Aldo

