The situation you describe that Aldo and Deena have tried to help you
with is difficult to accept as true without additional information.
The implications for all of us who run private groups is serious if
any of this is true, so permit me to be very skeptical of all of it.

Nowhere in this thread do you say that these e-mail messages going to
all members, which are not archived, come from or through the Google
Group, that is, they bear the Google Groups address. From what you
say, the messages seem not to come from the Group but rather from one
private email address, as Deena supposed, and so do I. The only
conclusion I can draw from that is that your entire membership list
has been copied by that person some time in the past. Also you do not
indicate whether or not your group is moderated and whether or not you
are the sole manager/list-owner. If it is moderated and non-subscribed
messages were actually were passing through Google Groups to your
Group, that would stop them in the message queue. You also do not say
if you have asked the person who has done this twice with an
unsubscribed e-mail address if he knows this is happening and why and
how he is doing it. He may have his email addresses linked in some
way. Or perhaps the e-mail addresses differ by a single character and
you have discovered a weakness in Google Group protocols. I'd read the
complete headers of those messages very carefully. It seems to me that
you should inquire of the purported sender.

In a group which is truly closed, as you say yours is, it should not
be possible for anyone, member or not, to used an e-mail address which
is not subscribed to the group to send mail through the group. If what
you say happened is possible, it should be happening in other groups.
In 4 years and many thousands of emails it has not happened once in my
group. This is the first account I have read of it happening in other
groups, which are larger and more active than mine. However, a message
sent with the spoofed e-mail address of a member will get as far as
the message moderation queue and on through to the members in an
unmoderated group.

